.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Wait until the event queue specified is non-empty.
If \f[C]ret_event\f[R] is not NULL, the first event in the queue will be
copied into \f[C]ret_event\f[R] and removed from the queue.
If \f[C]ret_event\f[R] is NULL the first event is left at the head of
the queue.
